Use the standard library
This is how to smallest_change of arr:
   Remember that n is arr's length
   Remember that half is quotient of n and 2
   Remember that count is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this half times:
      Remember that j is diff of (diff of n and 1) and i
      When item i in arr is not item j in arr, then:
         Increase count
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is count
Now you know
>>> smallest_change of [1, 2, 3, 5, 4, 7, 9, 6] 
4
>>> smallest_change of [1, 2, 3, 4, 3, 2, 2] 
1
>>> smallest_change of [1, 2, 3, 2, 1] 
0